To run a command as administrator (user "root"), use "sudo <command>".
See "man sudo_root" for details.

recruits@recruits-All-Series:~$ ls
Desktop  Documents  Downloads  Music  Pictures  Public  Templates  Videos
recruits@recruits-All-Series:~$ pwd
/home/recruits
recruits@recruits-All-Series:~$ mkdir workspace
recruits@recruits-All-Series:~$ cd workspace
recruits@recruits-All-Series:~/workspace$ ls
recruits@recruits-All-Series:~/workspace$ touch README.md
recruits@recruits-All-Series:~/workspace$ cp README.md CHANGELOG.md
recruits@recruits-All-Series:~/workspace$ ls
CHANGELOG.md  README.md
recruits@recruits-All-Series:~/workspace$ 
